===Etymology===
From {{AGr.}} {{polytonic|[[δῆμος]]|}} (dēmos) ''country'' + {{polytonic|[[ὄνυμα]]}} (onuma) ''name''. Possibly coined or revived in 1997 by Paul Dickonson of [[w:Merriam-Webster|Merriam-Webster]] in a manner similar to other [[-nym]]s.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{semantics}} A name for an [[inhabitant]] or [[native]] of a [[specific]] [[place]] that is derived from the [[name]] of the place.
#: ''Why is it that people from the United States use American as their '''demonym'''?''
# {{obsolete}} A [[pseudonym]] formed of an [[adjective]].
#: ''The Logophile has my favourite '''demonym''', I would write under it if he didn't.''

====Usage notes====
Although demonyms are capitalized in English, they are [[common noun]]s, not [[proper noun]]s.

